name: Times Square
description: New York City, NY Endless streams of shiny yellow cabs are glazed under a neon canopy of milky light as a pulsating sea of people converge at the crossroads of the world. Times Square is the world's most visited tourist attraction, with more than 39 million visitors annually. The city seen for the first time, in its first wild promise of all the mystery and the beauty in the world. -F. Scott Fitzgerald The buildings are shimmering verticality, a gossamer veil, a festive scene-prop hanging there against the black sky to dazzle, entertain, amaze. -Frank Lloyd Wright I carry the place around the world in my heart, but sometimes I try to shake it off in my dreams. -F. Scott Fitzgerald Vehement silhouettes of Manhattan - that vertical city with unimaginable diamonds. -Le Corbusier

name: Swiss Alps
description: En route to Southern Africa from Europe, before the lush greenery of the Congo and the vast bright Sahara, lie the Swiss Alps.

name: Autumn Snow
description:
Guelph, Ontario

Winter comes suddenly with an unexpected flurry, as vibrant yellow leaves cling on for their last chance of golden autumn glory.

name: Camps Bay Sunset
description:
Cape Town, South Africa

With its breathtaking sunset views of the Atlantic Ocean, Camps Bay is an affluent suburb of Cape Town, South Africa. It has a trendy nightlife and is famous for its white sandy beaches fringed by palm trees. 

Towering over the bay are the magnificent Twelve Apostles, a famous range of jagged, highly erosion-resistant Ordovician quartzitic sandstone cliffs that line the back of the Table Mountain Range.

The first residents of Camps Bay were the San hunter-gatherers and Khoi pastorates. When Jan van Riebeek first established a station for the Dutch East India Company, Camps Bay was covered in forests filled with lion, leopard and antelope.

Camps Bay was incorporated into Cape Town in 1913.

name: Kirstenbosch
description:
Camphor Avenue
Kirstenbosch National Botanical Garden
Cape Town, South Africa

"THE MOST BEAUTIFUL GARDEN IN AFRICA"

Kirstenbosch National Botanical Garden is acclaimed as one of the great botanical gardens of the world. Few gardens can match the sheer grandeur of the setting of Kirstenbosch against the Eastern slopes of Cape Town’s Table Mountain.

Kirstenbosch was established in 1913 to promote, conserve and display the extraordinarily rich and diverse flora of Southern Africa, and was the first botanical garden in the world to be devoted to a country's indigenous flora. Kirstenbosch displays a wide variety of the unique plant life of the Cape Flora, as well as plants from all the diverse regions of Southern Africa, both outdoors and in the Botanical Society Conservatory. There are more than 7,000 species in cultivation at Kirstenbosch, including many rare and threatened species.

The garden covers 36 hectares in a 528-hectare estate that contains protected mountainside, supporting natural forest and fynbos, along with a variety of animals and birds. Kirstenbosch lies in the heart of the Cape Floristic Region, also known as the Cape Floral Kingdom. In 2004, the Cape Floristic Region, including Kirstenbosch, was declared a UNESCO World Heritage Site; another first for Kirstenbosch, it is the first botanical garden in the world to be included within a natural World Heritage Site.

Kirstenbosch is the largest of a country-wide network of nine National Botanical Gardens administered by the South African National Biodiversity Institute (SANBI). Their mission is to promote the sustainable use, conservation, appreciation and enjoyment of the exceptionally rich plant and animal life of South Africa, for the benefit of all people.

name: Kobo Kobo Hills
description: Namibia Kobo Kobo Hills is a rustic and restful retreat at the foot of the Khomas Hochland Mountains in central Namibia, situated halfway between Windhoek and the coast, on the edge of the Namib Desert. Access to the camp is by prior arrangement only. The peace, quiet and distance from civilization makes for a perfect setting for any kind of getaway. http://www.kobokobo.com.na/

name: Ruacana Falls
description: Heavenly light pierces the mist of the mighty Kunene River at Ruacana Falls at the border of Angola and Namibia.

name: Caribbean Cave
description: Santo Domingo, Dominican Republic The Cave of the Three Eyes (Cueva de los Tres Ojos) is a collapsed cave featuring three small pools located on the outskirts of Santo Domingo. It was formed centuries ago when a series of underground caves collapsed, forming a bowl-shaped depression. The first of the three pools is named “the sulfur pool” and is a brilliant blue color when lit by direct sunlight.

name: Isla Saona
description: Dominican Republic, Caribbean Saona Island (Isla Saona in Spanish, baptized by Christopher Columbus, who discovered it in May, 1494 during his second voyage to the Americas) is a tropical island located a short distance from the mainland on the South-Eastern tip of the Dominican Republic, near La Altagracia Province. It is a government-protected nature reserve and is part of East National Park (Parque Nacional del Este). The island is famous for the natural beauty of its beaches and crystal clear, pristine waters. The seas around the island are rich in wildlife, with many species of birds and tropical marine fish. There are large areas where natural sandbars offshore bring the depth to just a few feet.

name: Chapman's Peak
description:
Western Cape, South Africa

The Chapman’s Peak drive is one of the most spectacular marine drives in the world. It winds its way between Noordhoek and Hout Bay on the Atlantic Coast on the South-Western tip of South Africa. The nine-kilometre route, with its 114 curves, skirts the rocky coastline of Chapman’s Peak (593m), which is the southerly extension of Constantiaberg.

Hacked out of the face of the mountain between 1915 and 1922, the road was at the time regarded as a major feat of engineering. Chapman's Peak Drive was closed in the 1990s, after a rockfall caused a death and a subsequent lawsuit. It re-opened after being re-engineered to protect motorists from falling rocks. The road was again closed for a number of months beginning on June 19, 2008 "as a result of risk areas identified on the mountain above the road", but has since been re-opened indefinitely.

The top of Chapman's Peak consists of flat, sedimentary rocks related to those that form Table Mountain. The base of the mountain, however, consists of Cape Granite and the two formations meet at a geological unconformity that is world-famous amongst earth scientists. Two different endangered vegetation types can be found along this road, which correspond to the two main geological formations. Peninsula Sandstone Fynbos and Cape Granite Fynbos are both endemic to the city of Cape Town, and occur nowhere else in the world.

name: Gondolas In The Night
description: Venice, Italy Resembling long-beaked Venetian masks of the Carnevale, these Gondolas perch on the shores of Venice like mythical, 17th Century beasts of the night.

name: Cafe
description: Venice, Italy

name: Table Mountain
description: Bloubergstrand (Blue Mountain Beach) in Cape Town, South Africa provides some of the most magnificent sunset views of Table Mountain.

name: Eye Of The Lion
description: A full body shot would never have given justice to the strength and magnificence of this fully-grown male lion in Grootfontein, Namibia. To properly see these things, we must look closer.

name: Central Park
description: Central Park, when the dirty end of winter meets the fresh breath of spring.

description:
Black Rhino, Etosha National Park

name: Lovers In Japan
description: Chris Martin of Coldplay Viva La Vida Tour Rogers Centre, Toronto, Canada The Viva la Vida Tour was the fourth concert tour by British band Coldplay and was in support of their fourth studio album, "Viva la Vida or Death and All His Friends". It was a massive critical and commercial success that visited Europe, Asia, the Americas and Australasia. The tour further secured Coldplay as one of the music industry's biggest draws and one of the world's most popular bands. For Coldplay fans around the globe, the image of frontman Chris Martin engulfed in a flurry of colourful butterflies is a timeless one. It captures the essence of one of the world's greatest bands at the height of their success. SOLD. Please contact Coldplay management for further information.

name: Venetian Kiss
description: Piazza San Marco, Venice, Italy A cool autumn night in a piazza filled with laughter and music. A tiny moment of affection echoes into eternity. Venezia, città dell'amore.

name: Cango Caves
description:
Oudtshoorn, South Africa

The Cango Caves are located in Precambrian limestones at the foothills of the Swartberg Mountains near the town of Oudtshoorn, in the Western Cape Province of South Africa. In this spectacular underground wonder of the Klein Karoo, you will find some of the world's finest dripstone caverns with their vast halls and towering formations.

The principal cave is one of the country's finest and best-known. Although the extensive system of tunnels and chambers goes on for over four kilometers, only about a quarter of this is open to visitors.

A visit to the caves consists of crawling through narrow passages and climbing up steep rock formations, guided by small lights. The caves contain breathtaking halls and grand limestone formations. The smallest passage that visitors will have to pass through is just under 30 cm high.

This magnificent labyrinth of interconnected chambers filled with stalagmites and helictites is truly one of the wonders of the world.

name: The Namib
description: The Namib Desert, Namibia "VAST PLACE" The Namib Desert is the oldest desert in the world and stretches for more than 2,000 kilometres (1,200 mi) along the Atlantic coast of Angola, Namibia, and South Africa, extending southward from the Carunjamba River in Angola, through Namibia and to the Olifants River in Western Cape, South Africa. The Namib is almost completely uninhabited by humans, with the exception of several small settlements and indigenous pastoral groups, including the Ovahimba and Obatjimba Herero in the North, and the Topnaar Nama in the central region. Owing to its antiquity, the Namib may be home to more endemic species than any other desert in the world. The name Namib is of Nama origin, and means "vast place".

name: Fallen Beast
description: Namib-Naukluft National Park, Namibia The Namib-Naukluft National Park extends over a large part of the Namib Desert and with an overall area of 49,768 km², it is the largest game reserve in Africa. Limited access to the park is either by dust roads or light aircraft. The park has some of the most unusual wildlife and nature reserves in the world, with an area larger than Switzerland (41,285 km²) and roughly the size of the US states New Hampshire and Vermont combined. The region is characterized by high, isolated inselbergs and kopjes (the Afrikaans term for rocky outcrops), made up of dramatic blood red granites, rich in feldspars and sandstone. The easternmost part of the park covers the Naukluft Mountains. The Namib Desert gave its name to Namibia - "the land of open spaces".

name: Venetian Canal
description:
Venice, Italy

"You may have the universe, if I may have Italy." -Giuseppe Verdi

name: Chicago At Night
description:
Chicago, IL

"WINDY CITY"

Chicago is the largest city in the U.S. state of Illinois, and the third most populous city in the United States, with approximately 2.7 million residents. Chicago was named a town in 1833, near a portage between the Great Lakes and the Mississippi River watershed. Today, the city retains its status as a major hub for industry, telecommunications and infrastructure, with O'Hare International Airport being the second busiest airport in the world in terms of traffic movements. In 2008, the city hosted 45.6 million domestic and overseas visitors.

The city's notoriety has found expression in numerous forms of popular culture, including novels, plays, movies, songs, various types of journals, and the news media.

name: Boston At Night
description:
Boston, MA

A historic American city bathes in dusk as daytime surrenders to an empire of city lights.

name: Lion's Head At Night
description: Cape Town, South Africa A protruding mountain of oddly-shaped rock named Lion's Head towers over the community of Camps Bay, backlit by Cape Town city bowl.

name: Camps Bay
description:
Camps Bay, South Africa

Nighttime rolls in with the ocean mist over the beach community of Camps Bay, enveloped by the Twelve Apostles on one side and the Atlantic Ocean on the other.

name: All Shall Be Equal...
description:
Cape Town, South Africa

An aging wall of graffiti reminds passersby of the motto that has governed a new South Africa for almost two decades. Eloquent wisdom and witty catchphrases often adorn street murals and can be witnessed throughout the city, if you keep your eyes open.

name: Place Of No Return
description: Sossusvlei, Namibia "PLACE OF NO RETURN" In the eerie silence of a desert pan deep in the ancient Namib, a long-gone community of dead trees stand frozen in time - relics of a world long gone. The Deadvlei of Sossusvlei is truly one of the most remarkable places on Earth. All the trees here, though dead, have been nearly perfectly preserved for centuries: there is not even moisture enough for normal decomposition to occur. Located in the Namib Naukluft park, the largest conservation area in Africa (and fourth largest in the world), the sand dunes of Sossusvlei in the Namib Desert are the highest dunes in the world. Sossusvlei is a mud pan created by a river that flows through the Namib every five to ten years. The river never reaches the Atlantic Ocean, but drains away between the dunes of Sossusvlei. The meaning of Sossus is "place of no return" and walking among these ancient ghosts, it is easy to see why.

name: Noordhoek
description:
Western Cape, South Africa

A peaceful equestrian community in the greater Cape Town area, Noordhoek offers a relaxed countryside-getaway from the hustle and bustle of the city. Fresh food and shopping awaits those who stumble upon the quaint Noordhoek Farm Village, surrounded by vineyards and horse farms.

name: Canal At Night
description:
Venice, Italy

Best experienced by strolling through the countless winding streets of the city, the colours and sights of Venice can offer a world of memories.

name: Fire In The Sky
description:
Waterberg Plateau, Namibia

Distant winds set the sky ablaze on a warm Namibian morning at the foot of Waterberg Plateau.

name: Park At Night
description:
Guelph, Ontario

Tungsten light warms the green giants of Royal City Park on a cool summer night.

name: Speed River At Night
description:
Guelph, ON, Canada

The stillness of the Speed River and the silence of the trees that frill its shores are perfect reasons to enjoy a midnight stroll through the peaceful sanctuary that is Guelph's Royal City Park.

name: Alley At Night
description: Guelph, Ontario

name: Giraffe
description:
Etosha, Namibia

Giraffes - magnificent in appearance, bizarre in form, unique in gait, colossal in height and inoffensive in character. An unmistakable silhouette treads silently through the bush of the Etosha pan, soaking up the last rays of the sun.

name: Springbok
description:
Etosha, Namibia

A springbok rests in a sea of yellow, always mindful of impending doom; for death is undeterred, no matter how idyllic the setting.

name: Gondolas After Dinner
description:
Venice, Italy

In the evening, the smell of spices and freshly cooked food oozes through the alleys of this historic city. After-dinner gondola rides are offered in just about every one of Venice's endless maze of canals.
